Package: transferaudit
Type: Package
Title: In-Vivo Transferability Audit of Transcriptomic Signatures
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Wendi", "Dou", email = "miya1337@mimoe.org",
    role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0009-0008-2815-3726"))
Description: A small, dependency-light toolkit for auditing whether an in-vitro
    (or otherwise derived) transcriptomic signature localises to its expected
    cell compartment in single-cell reference atlases. It computes a calibrated
    Transferability Score: the signature's compartment-localisation z-score
    relative to a size-matched random-gene-set permutation null. Developed for a
    dental mesenchymal-stromal-cell osteogenic program audited in human MRONJ and
    mouse jaw atlases, but applicable to any signature x compartment x atlas.
